 US scientists say they've found the earliest known case
 of AIDS.
 An African man who died of the disease in nineteen fifty-nine.
 The scientists at Rockefeller University in New York say they
 found clear signs of the HIV virus which causes AIDS in a
 blood sample taken from a man living in what is now Kinshasa in
 the democratic republic of Congo.
